-- First Bank Bids for Failed Nigerian Lender, Needs to Buy at `Right Price'
-- B y   R e n e e   B o n o r c h i s
-- 2010-10-04T13:02:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-04/first-bank-bids-for-failed-nigerian-lender-needs-to-buy-at-right-price-.html
First Bank of Nigeria Plc has bid for
one of the nation’s failed lenders, Oluyemisi Lanre-Phillips,
head of investor relations for the Lagos-based lender, said at a
conference in Johannesburg today.  “We’ve got the right bank but we need to get it at the
right price,” she said at the conference, hosted by Nedbank
Group Ltd.’s Nedbank Capital unit and Royal Bank of Scotland
Plc.  To contact the reporter on this story:
